\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Quantum coherence fields vary systematically across brain regions.} (\textbf  {A}) Regional field magnitude: R5 exhibits maximum (0.0482), R0 minimum (0.0184), mean 0.0278. (\textbf  {B}) Regional quantum coherence: R2 highest (7.20 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), R1 lowest (1.63 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), mean 3.71 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$. All values $\\ll$ 1 confirming rapid decoherence. (\textbf  {C}) Phase-magnitude space (polar coordinates) showing regional clustering: R0-R4 (purple-cyan) cluster at low magnitude (0.2-0.4), R5-R9 (green-yellow) at higher magnitude (0.6-0.8). (\textbf  {D-E}) Ion contributions: H$^+$ dominates all regions with zero field magnitude for Na$^+$, K$^+$, Ca$^{2+}$, Mg$^{2+}$ across all 10 regions. (\textbf  {F-G}) Region 0 distributions: magnitude mean 0.0231, phase mean -0.1539 rad. (\textbf  {H}) Magnitude vs coherence scatter plot showing no correlation (R$^2$ $\\approx$ 0), indicating independent regional dynamics. (\textbf  {I}) Ion field strength heatmap confirming H$^+$ exclusivity (orange) with zero contribution from other ions (blue) across all regions. Summary box: 10 regions analyzed, coherence time 10.0 $\\mu$s, average magnitude 0.02780, coherence range 1.63-7.20 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$. Interpretation confirms weak, transient quantum coherence supporting classical network dynamics as consciousness substrate.}}{14}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:coherence_overview}{{3}{14}{\textbf {Quantum coherence fields vary systematically across brain regions.} (\textbf {A}) Regional field magnitude: R5 exhibits maximum (0.0482), R0 minimum (0.0184), mean 0.0278. (\textbf {B}) Regional quantum coherence: R2 highest (7.20 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), R1 lowest (1.63 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), mean 3.71 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$. All values $\\ll$ 1 confirming rapid decoherence. (\textbf {C}) Phase-magnitude space (polar coordinates) showing regional clustering: R0-R4 (purple-cyan) cluster at low magnitude (0.2-0.4), R5-R9 (green-yellow) at higher magnitude (0.6-0.8). (\textbf {D-E}) Ion contributions: H$^+$ dominates all regions with zero field magnitude for Na$^+$, K$^+$, Ca$^{2+}$, Mg$^{2+}$ across all 10 regions. (\textbf {F-G}) Region 0 distributions: magnitude mean 0.0231, phase mean -0.1539 rad. (\textbf {H}) Magnitude vs coherence scatter plot showing no correlation (R$^2$ $\\approx$ 0), indicating independent regional dynamics. (\textbf {I}) Ion field strength heatmap confirming H$^+$ exclusivity (orange) with zero contribution from other ions (blue) across all regions. Summary box: 10 regions analyzed, coherence time 10.0 $\\mu$s, average magnitude 0.02780, coherence range 1.63-7.20 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$. Interpretation confirms weak, transient quantum coherence supporting classical network dynamics as consciousness substrate}{figure.3}{}}
\newlabel{fig:coherence_overview@cref}{{[figure][3][]3}{[1][13][]14}}
