\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {H$^+$ coherence fields exhibit spatial structure enabling categorical completion.} (\textbf  {A}) Regional field magnitude map (Region 0) showing spatial gradient from 0.000 to 0.030 (arbitrary units). Peak magnitude (yellow) at coordinates (1.5, 0.5) indicates oscillatory hole location. (\textbf  {B}) Phase distribution revealing coherent phase structure centered at $\phi \approx 0$ rad with spatial extent $\sim $2 a.u. (\textbf  {C}) H$^+$ substrate strength across four brain regions (R0-R3): R0 exhibits highest field magnitude (0.139), establishing it as primary consciousness substrate region. (\textbf  {D}) Ion contributions showing H$^+$ dominance (0.15 field magnitude) over Na$^+$ (0.01), K$^+$ (0.02), Ca$^{2+}$ (0.09), and Mg$^{2+}$ (0.14). (\textbf  {E}) Regional coherence levels: R2 shows maximum coherence (7.20 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), R0 and R3 intermediate (6.40 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$, 2.61 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), R1 minimum (1.63 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$). (\textbf  {F}) Complex field structure in phase space showing density distribution (blue) with localized peaks (red markers) corresponding to categorical completion sites. Spatial heterogeneity enables parallel categorical processing across brain regions.}}{17}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:coherence_fields}{{4}{17}{\textbf {H$^+$ coherence fields exhibit spatial structure enabling categorical completion.} (\textbf {A}) Regional field magnitude map (Region 0) showing spatial gradient from 0.000 to 0.030 (arbitrary units). Peak magnitude (yellow) at coordinates (1.5, 0.5) indicates oscillatory hole location. (\textbf {B}) Phase distribution revealing coherent phase structure centered at $\phi \approx 0$ rad with spatial extent $\sim $2 a.u. (\textbf {C}) H$^+$ substrate strength across four brain regions (R0-R3): R0 exhibits highest field magnitude (0.139), establishing it as primary consciousness substrate region. (\textbf {D}) Ion contributions showing H$^+$ dominance (0.15 field magnitude) over Na$^+$ (0.01), K$^+$ (0.02), Ca$^{2+}$ (0.09), and Mg$^{2+}$ (0.14). (\textbf {E}) Regional coherence levels: R2 shows maximum coherence (7.20 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), R0 and R3 intermediate (6.40 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$, 2.61 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$), R1 minimum (1.63 $\times $ 10$^{-4}$). (\textbf {F}) Complex field structure in phase space showing density distribution (blue) with localized peaks (red markers) corresponding to categorical completion sites. Spatial heterogeneity enables parallel categorical processing across brain regions}{figure.4}{}}
